Note: if you have closed the Inspector, secondary click on the object (in Desktop mode, target the object with your laser and press CTRL+R), open your Context Menu (in Desktop mode: CTRL+T), and select "Open Inspector"
1.  Reselect the "Meshes (Scale Me)" object
2.  Create a child object
3.  Rename child to "Numbers"
4.  Click on the "copy" icon to duplicate it
5.  Select the new "Numbers" slot and rename it to "Numbers Pivot"
6.  Open Context Menu and select "Create New"
7.  Select "Text"
8.  Select "Outline"
9.  Click on the pencil icon and change the text to "12"
10.  Secondary-select the object, open up the Context Menu, and select "Open Inspector"
11. Change the name to "12"
12. Scroll to the "Grabbable" component and deselect "Enabled"
13. Drag the 12 slot into the "Meshes (Scale Me") slot
14. Select the 12 slot and click on "Position" and "Rotation"
15. Set Position (y) to "0.6"
16. Click on the "copy" icon to duplicate the 12 slot
17. Change value of "Text" to "1"
18. Change the name of the slot to "1"
19: Drag the 1 slot into the "Numbers Pivot" slot
20: Select the "Numbers Pivot" slot and change its rotation on z to "-30". Don't confuse the position field for the rotation field (but if you do, you can undo it)
21: Open up the "Numbers Pivot" slot and drag the 1 slot into the "Numbers" slot
22: Reset the rotation on the "Numbers Pivot" slot
23: Repeat steps 15-21 to create and rotate "2"
24: Do the same for 3, but before moving it out of "Numbers" Pivot, Select "3" and change its rotation on Z to "90"
25: Then move "3" into the "Numbers" slot and reset the rotation of the "Numbers Pivot" slot
26: Follow the same process to create and rotate "4" and "5", but instead of rotating them on z to "90" as you did for "3", rotate them by 180
27: Do not forget to move your finished "Numbers" to the "Numbers" slot and reset the rotation of the "Numbers Pivot" slot
28: Drag "12" into the "Numbers" slot
29: Double-click on the "Numbers" slot and click on the "copy" icon to duplicate it
30: Drag the new "Numbers" slot into the "Numbers Pivot" slot
31: Set the rotation on z for the "Numbers Pivot" slot to 180
32: Open up the "Numbers Pivot"and "Numbers" slots to select the new "12" slot
33: Change the rotation on z for the "12" slot to 180
34: Change the name of the slot to "6" and change its text to read "6" as well
35: Drag the finished "6" slot into the "Numbers" slot
36: You will repeat this process to change the duplicated numbers.  Set z rotations for the "Numbers" by adding 180 to their current values, as follows:
- 7: "-210"
- 8: "-240"
- 9: "0"
-10: "240"
-11: "210"
37: Once you have dragged "11" into the "Numbers" slot, use the "recycle" icon to delete the "Numbers Pivot" slot
